# SDD Rules

## Before writing ANY code
1. Read the relevant spec file in `specs/<feature>/`
2. If no spec exists, STOP and tell the user to create one first
3. Only implement what is explicitly stated in requirements.md and design.md
4. Do not add "nice to have" features, over-engineer, or add security layers unless stated

## Task execution
- Only implement the ONE task given to you
- Write tests BEFORE implementation (TDD)
- After finishing a task, summarize what was done and what test covers it
- Do not read tasks.md in full — only process the task given in the prompt

## Decision log
- If you make any design decision not explicitly covered in the spec, add it to `specs/<feature>/decision_log.md`

## Scope
- When in doubt, do LESS not more
- This is not an enterprise product unless the spec says so
- Repo source code of each module/service always has Makefile to run on local

## Documentation
- Update ONBOARDING.md for when anything change that related to onboarding new member
- Update AGENT.md for helping agent understand the code base on new task